{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-classic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-150-searching-a-triangular-array-for-a-sub-triangle-having-minimum-sum","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"project-euler-problems-101-to-200","demoType":null,"title":"","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>U trougaonom nizu koji sadrži pozitivne i negativne cele brojeve želimo da pronađemo podtrougao čiji je zbir elemenata najmanji moguć.</p>\n<p>U primeru ispod, lako je dokazati da navedeni trougao zadovoljava ovaj uslov jer ima zbir od −42.</p>\n<img alt=\"Trougaoni niz sa istaknutim podtrouglom čiji je zbir -42\" src=\"https://cdn.freecodecamp.org/curriculum/project-euler/searching-a-triangular-array-for-a-sub-triangle-having-minimum-sum.gif\" style=\"background-color: white; padding: 10px; display: block; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; margin-bottom: 1.2rem;\">\n<p>Želimo da napravimo trougaoni niz sa hiljadu redova, pa generišemo 500500 pseudo-slučajnih brojeva $s_k$ u opsegu $±2^{19}$ koristeći varijantu generatora pseudo-slučajnih brojeva (poznatu kao Linear Congruential Generator) na sledeći način:</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{align}\nt := &#x26; \\ 0\\\\\n\\text{kwa}\\ &#x26; k = 1\\ \\text{hadi}\\ k = 500500:\\\\\n&#x26; t := (615949 × t + 797807)\\ \\text{modulo}\\ 2^{20}\\\\\n&#x26; s_k := t − 219\\\\\n\\end{align}$$</p>\n<p>Dakle: $s_1 = 273519$, $s_2 = −153582$, $s_3 = 450905$ n.k.</p>\n<p>Naš trougaoni niz formira se korišćenjem ovih pseudo-slučajnih brojeva na sledeći način:</p>\n<p>$$\ns_1 \\\\\ns_2\\;s_3 \\\\\ns_4\\; s_5\\; s_6 \\\\\ns_7\\; s_8\\; s_9\\; s_{10} \\\\\n\\ldots\n$$</p>\n<p>Podtrouglovi mogu početi od bilo kog elementa niza i širiti se naniže koliko god želimo (uzimajući dva elementa neposredno ispod u sledećem redu, zatim tri u narednom redu i tako dalje).</p>\n<p>\"Zbir malog trougla\" je definisan kao zbir svih elemenata koji su unutar njega.</p>\n<p>Pronađi najmanji mogući zbir podtrougla.</p>\n</section>","id":"5900f4031000cf542c50ff15","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":"","notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"Euler","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"project-euler","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":301781,"hooks":null,"fields":{"slug":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-150-searching-a-triangular-array-for-a-sub-triangle-having-minimum-sum"},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"function smallestSubTriangleSum() {\n\n  return true;\n}\n\nsmallestSubTriangleSum();","head":null,"tail":null,"editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["script.js"]}],"saveSubmissionToDB":null,"tests":[{"text":"<p><code>smallestSubTriangleSum()</code> inapaswa kurudisha <code>-271248680</code>.</p>","testString":"assert.strictEqual(smallestSubTriangleSum(), -271248680);"}]}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/project-euler/#project-euler-problems-101-to-200","dashedName":"problem-150-searching-a-triangular-array-for-a-sub-triangle-having-minimum-sum","certification":"project-euler","disableLoopProtectTests":true,"disableLoopProtectPreview":true,"superBlock":"project-euler","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"project-euler-problems-101-to-200","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-151-paper-sheets-of-standard-sizes-an-expected-value-problem","prevChallengePath":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-200/problem-149-searching-for-a-maximum-sum-subsequence","id":"5900f4031000cf542c50ff15","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeData":{"challengeType":1,"challengeFiles":[{"name":"script","ext":"js","contents":"// solution required","history":["script.js"],"fileKey":"scriptjs"}]}},"id":"/learn/project-euler/project-euler-problems-101-to-2